pr_title: Move production suites fromTravis to circle ci
pr_body:
Moving Production suites to Circle CI.

Tested on Circle CI:smiley:

Followups 
1. Figure out how will we handle cache storing since now cache is both for production and development(till now cache key is dependent on development requirements )
2. Do some profiling on making these tests more efficient. (Probably use a new bionic docker image for production)
3. Clear travis hack code for adding travis path in our codebase.

@timabbott @amanagr Could you have a look at this?

We just also need to install it directly in the setup script because we need it before puppet is run.", 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2020, 5, 26, 22, 13, 53, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'timabbott', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 430751385, 'comment_body': 'Why *do* we use it before Puppet is run? Wouldnâ€™t it make more sense to have a Puppet class for `certbot` that configures everything inside Puppet?', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2020, 5, 26, 22, 55, 10, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'andersk', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 430877083, 'comment_body': "Hmm, good question.  My guess is that it's a bit of a chicken-and-egg problem.  To use certbot in the standalone mode, we need nginx to not be running when we run certbot, which is kinda a messy thing to setup in puppet.  Or to use it in webroot mode, we need nginx running, but it won't start until a certificate is provided.  

(And I think we didn't have proper support for the `webroot` mode when we first added the tool)

What we don't want is `nginx` to fail to start because the certificate isn't available yet.

So there's probably a world where we make the installer:
(1) The --certbot option doesn't run certbot, it just sets `zulip.conf` to do so in puppet and then sets up the self-signed cert
(2) Then puppet manages the dance of running certbot in webroot mode

But that would probably end up being worse; `puppet` doesn't have the best error messages, so it's probably better to have `certbot` run from shell anyway for handling users providing a hostname they don't control (or whatever).", 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2020, 5, 27, 6, 7, 38, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'timabbott', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 431173591, 'comment_body': '@timabbott  Pushed the changes. pr_title: migrations: Upgrade migrations to remove duplicates in all Count tables.
pr_body:
Upgrades 0015_clear_duplicate_counts migration to remove
duplicate count in StreamCount, UserCount, InstallationCount as well.

Fixes https://github.com/zulip/docker-zulip/issues/266

Testing- 

Unapplied analytics 0015 and 0016 migrations with 
`
python manage.py migrate analytics 0014_remove_fillstate_last_modified
`

 Added duplicate values using python manage.py shell

for stat in list(COUNT_STATS.keys()): 

      for _ in range(2): 
           RealmCount.objects.create(property=stat, end_time=end_time, realm=r, subgroup=None, value=2) 
           UserCount.objects.create(property=stat, end_time=end_time, user=u, realm=r, subgroup=None, value=3) 
           StreamCount.objects.create(property=stat, end_time=end_time, stream=s, realm=r, subgroup=None, value=4) 
           InstallationCount.objects.create(property=stat, end_time=end_time, subgroup=None, value=4) 



Then replied the migration with 
`
python manage.py migrate
`
and checked that if there is still any duplicate present.
@timabbott  Can you check this?

Removed postgresql and python 2 packages when creating docker images
for Circle CI.
Rebuilt the images. 
Follow up to [https://github.com/zulip/zulip/pull/15534#issuecomment-648519122](https://github.com/zulip/zulip/pull/15534#issuecomment-648519122)
CI is failing with 
```
Error: Evaluation Error: Error while evaluating a Function Call, Could not find template 'zulip/postgresql//postgresql.conf.template.erb' (file: /home/circleci/zulip/puppet/zulip/manifests/postgres_appdb_tuned.pp, line: 33, column: 16) on node b22e07e6acc9.ec2.internal
 
Jun 24 13:55:52 
 
Jun 24 13:55:52 Zulip installation failed (exit code 1)!

```
I guess we have to merge this first.
[https://github.com/zulip/zulip/pull/15534/commits/03cf3087d7fede5f71896f77059e66696857870d](https://github.com/zulip/zulip/pull/15534/commits/03cf3087d7fede5f71896f77059e66696857870d)
@timabbott Ping.

pr_title: Update documentation for Bionic to Focal upgrade.
pr_body:
Tested Bionic to Focal upgrade on Digital Ocean Droplet.

We have to use this -d Flag till Focal first point release.

The first Ubuntu 20.04 point release is scheduled for release on August 6, 2020. [Source](https://www.omgubuntu.co.uk/2020/05/ubuntu-20-04-1-coming-july#:~:text=The%20first%20Ubuntu%2020.04%20point,to%20the%20distro%20since%20April.)
Follow up to [https://github.com/zulip/zulip/issues/14589#issuecomment-652711320](https://github.com/zulip/zulip/issues/14589#issuecomment-652711320)

@timabbott  Can you check this?

pr_review_comments: [{'comment_id': 416705494, 'comment_body': 'After this feature is added in zulipbot for Circle CI, we can replace it with Circle CI.', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2020, 4, 28, 15, 25, 34, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'arpit551', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 416823078, 'comment_body': 'Opened https://github.com/zulip/zulipbot/issues/172 to track this.', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2020, 4, 28, 18, 14, 7, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'timabbott', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 416832138, 'comment_body': "It's spelled `CircleCI`; I went ahead and added a commit to change this.", 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2020, 4, 28, 18, 28, 32, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'timabbott', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 416832425, 'comment_body': 'I fixed this space typo.', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2020, 4, 28, 18, 29, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'timabbott', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 416833151, 'comment_body': 'I didn\'t like this framing around "development and production environment"s -- the goal of testing is to ensure things work in production; the development environment exists almost entirely in service of that purpose.  The right framing is that we\'re running the test suites we can run in the development environment plus some end-to-end tests.', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2020, 4, 28, 18, 30, 7, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'timabbott', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 416833312, 'comment_body': 'I decided to remove this last block about helper scripts, and just have explanation above for how to find these.
